  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nAfter the entire audio message has been played timer isn't refreshed and the last second of the audio message is shown.\r\nAlso, timestamp looks like the length of the audio message.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nAfter playing the audio message, the timer shows 0:00.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n![ezgif com-resize (21)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/90643886-5c200300-e234-11ea-9430-b81eb0e9581e.gif)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open 1-1/group chat\r\n- Send audio message\r\n- Play audio message \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: Nightly 19/08\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n@errorists Could you recommend how to place the timestamp so it doesn't look like the length of the audio message?",
